Hide ITPs with no clickable evidence

1,316 of 1,669 ITPs had nothing on file beyond a UKPRN — no inspection
report, no compliance notice, no news. Surfacing them in the dashboard
was just noise: a sales rep clicking through landed on an empty detail
page with a name and tier and nothing to act on.

The dashboard now applies an "actionable" filter by default:
  * at least one Ofsted inspection with a report_url, OR
  * an active compliance notice, OR
  * a news item with trigger_severity >= 50.

Per-type effect:
  * ITPs:           1,669 -> 353 actionable
  * FE colleges:      233 ->  23 actionable
  * Sixth-form:        95 ->  69 actionable
  * Employers:        152 ->  12 actionable
  * Universities:     107 ->  ~95 actionable (apprenticeship_standards>=5
                                     also counts since uni's don't get
                                     Ofsted)

Where the filter applies:
  * /itps - all panels (critical, high, major providers, all-ITPs table)
  * /universities - all-unis table + tier counts
  * /opportunities - default view; ?show_all=1 query param disables the
    filter so the full register stays browsable when needed.

The headline tile on /itps now reads "Actionable ITPs · 353" with a
subtitle reminding the user that the underlying register still has
1,669 entries — they just don't appear in the working list until we
have something to click through to.
